In the Version Charts, when setting the Estimation Statistic to time (Original Time Estimate), the y-axis does not allow user to control the ticks and it probably should. It adjust the ticks to the nearest hour. The units seem to be hard coded in the FlotChartUtils.js file.

// round the minimum tick size to the nearest hour (values are in seconds)
var r = (minTickSize % 3600)

h3. Expected Behavior
Show tooltip with versions assigned to an issue when hovering over "x Versions" label of an issue in the Backlog of the board.

!tooltip_on_6.4.12_anon.png|thumbnail!

h3. Actual Behavior
As of JIRA 7.1.x, nothing is shown.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# In an Agile board, create two versions;
# Assign those versions to a single issue;
# Note that the issue will have a label "2 Versions";
# There is no way to see which versions those are without opening the "Issue Detail View";

I'm using the following code to create issues with a popup dialog. I want to create issues via HTML links such that the field value can be initilized in the form.

The dialog popups up, meanwhile after I click the create button, the dialog redirects to issue detail page and doesn't close. I need to close the dialog as soon as I click the create button.

Can someone help me? Thank you!

 

<html>

<head><meta name="decorator" content="atl.general">

<script type="text/javascript">

(function()\{

JIRA.bind(JIRA.Events.NEW_CONTENT_ADDED, function (e, $ctx) \{
initLargeDialogs($ctx);
});

function initLargeDialogs(context) \{
context.find("a.trigger-dialog-large").each(function () \{
new JIRA.FormDialog(\{
trigger: this,
id: this.id + "-dialog",
ajaxOptions: \{
url: this.href,
data: \{
decorator: "dialog",
inline: "true"
}
},
widthClass: "large"
});
});
}

})(jQuery)

</script>

</head>

<body>
<div>

<a id="createLink" class="aui-button aui-button-primary aui-style trigger-dialog-large"
href="/jira/secure/CreateIssueDetails!init.jspa?pid=10000&issuetype=10000&projectkey=one&summary=none&reporter=admin&assignee=admin&decorator=popup" >Create issue</a>
</div>

</body>
</html>

